 all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":62,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":71,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":106,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William de Dammartin was born in 1153, in Stoke, Devon, England. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with William De Dammartin of Cotton-Mendlesham."},"et":{"1153–":"1153–Surnud","1138–1195":"1138–1195","1165–1258":"1165–1258","1170–1225":"1170–1225","1153–Female":"1153–Surnud","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1225":"1225","1258":"1258","1224":"1224","1165":"1165","1153":"1153","1195":"1195","about 1165":"umbes 1165","1170":"1170","Stoke, Devon, England":"Stoke, Devon, England","of Norton Mandeville, Essex, England":"Nort